div.div: Commented on #6348 Proposal: Resource Update Control at Edge

While creating a new Pod upgrade workflow like OTA is certainly feasible—it enforces an upgrade only after explicit confirmation from the edge—it effectively bypasses the native behavior of Kubernetes resources like Deployments and DaemonSets. So this method cannot be directly applied within those native controllers. If we want to support upgrade control without changing how users interact with standard resources like Deployments or DaemonSets, we might need to hook into their reconciliation logic, intercept updates, and translate them into corresponding custom CRDs to be sent to the edge. This approach could enable confirmation-based upgrades within the standard resource framework but would likely require significant development effort. I'm not entirely sure if this line of thinking is correct,
